caption: During this shutdown they have great products for sale. Totally worth stopping in and buying all you can.

They do not fulfil online orders. Placed an order on seamless, paid, and they told the driver delivery driver that they would not make the order. Very "fishy". Had to call our credit card company to get a refund. Would avoid this business at all costs.
Great tasting food, but not worth the price!!! Portion is definitely too little for the money paid.

I don’t usually love restaurants with only high top seating and I don’t usually love seafood restaurants. So of course I loved St Julivert Fisherie.  Don’t miss the anchovies with vanilla butter or the Octopus carpaccio

The food was great, nothing amazing but it was good. The service was alright. They were very nice but our server didn’t know when to talk to guests, she cut off our conversation at least four times. I would go back again just to see if I would have a better time. My friends all liked it
Delicious seafood. As a sister restaurant to la Vera next door, it didn’t disappoint us. I would go back there again.
The food was amazing, really really good, 5 from 5 stars. But the portions are tiny for the very expensive price.
Wonderful surprise for Valentine's day ❣️ All dishes were super delicious! Music was nice and service friendly. Highlights were rum cake and beet cocktails 😋
The food is really good. We had a dinner right next to chef station. He’s fun, great conversation. He knows how to cook ! Definitely coming back.
friendly service. refreshing drinks. tasty, unique, and well-portioned dishes featuring fresh seafood. great ambiance, unpretentious, and you don’t have to shout to hold a conversation.

The pickled shrimp is everything! Really love this dish. We've been here a couple of times. I love la vara and it's owned by the same people. The first time was during their opening week and it was very busy and most of the food was very good but it seemed understandably harried. We went again and it was very chill. The service was excellent. it's nice to have a seafood restaurant at the neighborhood that has interesting and dishes that delight the eye and taste buds.
A really cool menu with a lot of delicious options in a great cozy space. I'm excited to come back!

A nice spot for when your in Brooklyn heights .. Its a bit close quarters in there and I'm sure reservations are preferred. Nice menu with shareable plates perfect for a date or a meeting with friends .the jerk hamachi collar should be on your list of things to get .
Food was barely ok. Prices and portions signal a Pretentiousness that is not balanced with the final outcome.
Fried clam strips were great, reminded me of HoJo's as a kid which is OK to this BOOMER !!

Amazingly delicious food, which kinda makes up for the insanely crowded tables. All tables are high tops (which is ok) but I literally had to climb over there aisle seat to get in next to the wall. Server was excellent and knowledgeable but don't drop anything on the floor or it's gone for good.

TIGHT QUARTERS UNFORTUNATELY REMINISCENT of rush hour on the nearby G subway line aside, Saint Julivert is a five-star place. Cuisine, inventiveness, staff and decor were all very, very good. An octopus carpaccio was plated beautifully, immediately easing our anxiety over the unfamiliar offering, and it tasted even better.  A plate called hamachi collar featured a crisped skin that was dreamy. Our servers were effective and charming and full of good guidance for seafood lovers and others.
Highly recommend. This is the kind of place you can choose from the menu being blindfolded and still be amazed with the selected dish. It is that good.
One of the best spots for seafood and delicious wines
Good food, excellent service and original, interesting dishes. Definitely worth a try for the curious. We sat in the back by the cook and asked for an omakase style feeding and she really delivered!
Good service. Delicious food. Nice atmosphere.

I've been a few times, the food is delicious but the service is a really mixed bag.  The bartenders are not welcoming and friendly, but relatively cold and pretentious.  For the price in the neighborhood, there are warmer spots to waste some hours with a glass of good wine.  Especially with what something like Eater might call an "inventive" menu (and others might call, at best, an *obscure* wine list), service is really the key to enjoying your meal, and finding what you are looking for in a hay stack of oddball varietals.  After having given saint julivert a couple chances (for the sake of the good eats), I'm just not sold its where I want to spend my money.  I think time will tell the same unless they reality check their payroll.

Surprisingly it wasn’t crowded on a Friday, maybe everyone was out of the town for the Labor Day long weekend. Inside are only high tables and bar seats, a mix of industrial and minimalism style. Rip and dip is a new item on the menu, veggie frittata with taro, peas, cilantros etc, the dipping sauce made the dish even better. Pig ear terrine is so tender that it was melting in the mouth very quickly. The swordfish belly has good amount to fat, which made the dish meat neither dry or plain. Cream spinach goes well with the fish. Service is great and the staff is very attentive.
Wow!! The whipped mackerel and hamachi collar were so so good. Customer service was excellent, the bartender was so lovely and attentive. Can’t wait to return!
Finest spot to buy some food when in a rush. Their customer service is fast, rates are fair, good atmosphere. Keep up the good work
Great service. Food is a bit too salty. Get the anchovies.
We wanted to like it...the service is wonderful and the space is small but very comfortable. The real issue is the food, which was —across the board— only okay.
Friendly staff and fish dishes to get excited about.
excellent neighborhood spot with interesting wines and tasty dishes. ask your server for recommendations.
Really delicious food. The ceviche was delicious and the squid ink "pasta" was surprisingly rich. Will come here again.

Creative and delicious small dishes. We were two and ordered a snack, two cold and two hot dishes. Service was good, a little slower for the hot dishes. Our waitress was superb. The atmosphere is much brighter than a typical NY restaurant and there are only stools to sit so it may not be easy for some older and heavily pregnant people. Highly recommend the food here. Great addition to the neighborhood.
While the food was often excellent, the service was terrible, and it was expensive for what it was.
Favorite neighborhood spot - the whipped makeral  is a must. Excellent wine selection.
Excellent food and great service. Will definitely be going back.
Nice ambiance and service. Food is unique but nothing wowed. Presentation beautiful.
Really impressed with this new addition to the neighborhood. Every dish was delicious - lots of variety and plays on more standard/traditional options. Desserts not quite as unique but delicious.
eater rec
Creative small plates of seafood, with a great wine selection. Most everything was delicious, with my favorites being the whipped mackerel, and the scallop tacos.
Unique menu and very helpful staff! Food was all delicious.
Excellent seafood and vibe. Great service
Superb!
A fantastic restaurant. Every dish was memorable. I cannot even recommend certain dishes as they were all great. Try to snag a seat by the kitchen if possible.

Delicious food. Every dish was tasty and had something a little unexpected to surprise and delight you. Average service - you get what you need. Prices are a little high but worth it for the flavors, creativity, and execution. STRONG recommend.
No ancient Chinese secret here. Just the best food in Chinatown. Vegetarian friendly options. Great service if you can get in. Worth the wait.

I don't usually do reviews but I felt I needed to since I had such a great experience at St Julivert. I do believe this is my new favorite restaurant in Brooklyn. I've gone several times and every time the menu has been  simply incredible. The octopus carpaccio and the raw scallops are a must try. I get the Kanpachi collar as well as the Sea Urchin every single time. My favorite drink experience is the Rum Ti' Punch. I don't usually drink rum but the way they serve it here I really love the experience.
Excellent seafood. The barnacles were fantastic.

Close your eyes and pretend for a moment that you are on your favorite trip by the sea, where you have wandered all day and you are hungry as ever for something memorable and authentic. And you stumble upon a glowing place on a quiet corner and start with a cocktail filled with promise. And then one by one, food comes out that delights and fulfills your tired day. Comforting, refined, delicious. This is the place I have always wanted in my neighborhood.

Spectacular. This crew nailed it again. Some of the most creative, delicious seafood in the city. We ate almost the entire menu, and not one dish disappointed. Beautifully composed seafood, varied flavors, perfectly executed. The drinks, service and vibe are all spot on as well. Already a tough table, deservedly so.
amazing tastes, great place! loved the octopus...
Amazing creative seafood and dishes!!

A nice addition to their good-food-corner of Clinton St., Saint Julivert is able to serve a complete menu of exclusively seafood. The results is a surprising flavourful journey that makes you rediscover the pleasure of fish dishes. If often fish happens to be the least interesting choice on a menu, what would you choose if you are on a diet, here it is all different and seafood is the king of taste. Spices and strong beautifully balanced flavours are at the center of attention supported by a good choice of wines. Not to mention that the place are all very very pretty, word of graphic designer.
